# Jorkin' Joel's BBQ Hole — Project Conventions

## Architecture
- **Theme** (`jjbbq-theme/`): visual presentation only — classic PHP templates, no FSE/block theme
- **Plugin** (`jjbbq-manager/`): all data structures (CPTs, ACF fields, admin UX)
- Theme reads from plugin via helper functions; never define CPTs in the theme

## PHP Standards
- PHP 8.0+ compatible syntax
- Text domain: `'jjbbq'` for all translatable strings
- Prefix all functions, hooks, handles: `jjbbq_`
- All ACF `get_field()` calls must have fallback values
- All `WP_Query` loops must call `wp_reset_postdata()`
- Enqueue handles use `jjbbq-` prefix

## Custom Post Types
- `jjbbq_event` — Pop-Up Events (slug: `pop-ups`)
- `jjbbq_menu_item` — Menu Items (slug: `menu-items`)

## Brand Colors (official — Photoshop samples: `reference-images/Initial Build and Client Identity/jjbbq-*.png`)
- Red: `#dd2c2f` · rgb(221, 44, 47)
- Gold / yellow: `#f7b112` · rgb(247, 177, 18)
- Pink light: `#fa968d` · rgb(250, 150, 141)
- Pink dark: `#fb4d51` · rgb(251, 77, 81)
- Black: `#000000`, White: `#ffffff`
- UI neutrals in theme: dark BG `#1a0000`, light/cream `#faf6f0`, text on red `#fff5e0` — see `assets/scss/_variables.scss`

## Brand Voice
- Bold, loud, unapologetic, local. Never corporate or delicate.
- The sell-out model is a feature, not a limitation.
